Projects

UTS Routing
UTS Routing uses real-time bus information from the University of Virginia to find the fastest route between two locations on grounds using the University Transportation System (UTS).
RaPID Photonics
The goal of RaPID Photonics was to create a photolithography prototyping device out of a standard Blu-ray drive, creating a photolithography equivalent to 3D printers.
Identifying Malware with Machine Learning
This project used a Decision Tree classifier to classify a set of programs as malware or goodware based on each program's sequence of API calls.
Tesla Coil
As an independent study in high school, I built a 12 kV Tesla Coil!
